#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:303
msgid ""
"To access credentials for the Axivox user portal, navigate to the top of "
"the :menuselection:`Permissions` tab. Then, copy the :guilabel:`Username`, "
"and enter the correct :guilabel:`Password` for the individual user. There is "
"a minimum of 8 characters for a user password."
msgstr ""
"For at få adgang til legitimationsoplysninger til Axivox-brugerportalen skal "
"du navigere til toppen af fanen :menuselection:`Tilladelser`. Kopiér "
"derefter :guilabel:`Brugernavn`, og indtast den korrekte "
":guilabel:`Adgangskode` for den enkelte bruger. Der er minimum 8 tegn til en "
"brugeradgangskode."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:309
msgid ""
"These are the same permissions granted to the Axivox administrator that are "
"listed in the menu on the left in the Axivox management console. Should a "
"selection state :guilabel:`No`, or :guilabel:`No access`, then the menu "
"option does **not** populate for the user."
msgstr ""
"Dette er de samme tilladelser, der gives til Axivox-administratoren, som er "
"opført i menuen til venstre i Axivox-administrationskonsollen. Hvis en "
"tilstand angiver :guilabel:`Nej` eller :guilabel:`Ingen adgang`, vises "
"menuindstillingen **ikke** for brugeren."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:316
msgid ""
"Upon finishing the setup for a new user, an :ref:`voip/axivox/"
"incoming_number` can be linked."
msgstr ""
"Når opsætningen for en ny bruger er færdig, kan et :ref:`voip/axivox/"
"incoming_number` tilknyttes."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:None
msgid ""
"Manage a user page, with the permissions tab highlighted, along with the "
"first permission\n"
"highlighted indicating a no selection."
msgstr ""
"Administrer en brugerside med fanen tilladelser fremhævet sammen med den "
"første tilladelse\n"
"fremhævet, som indikerer et valg af nej."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:326
msgid "User groups"
msgstr "Brugergrupper"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:328
msgid ""
"A user group is a grouping of Axivox users that can be linked to a queue for "
"call center capability."
msgstr ""
"En brugergruppe er en gruppering af Axivox-brugere, der kan tilknyttes en kø "
"til callcenter-funktionalitet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:331
msgid ""
"To begin using user groups, navigate to `https://manage.axivox.com <https://"
"manage.axivox.com>`_."
msgstr ""
"For at begynde at bruge brugergrupper skal du navigere til `https://"
"manage.axivox.com <https://manage.axivox.com>`_."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:333
msgid ""
"Then, log in with the appropriate administrator credentials. From the menu "
"on the left of the Axivox administrative panel, click into :guilabel:`User "
"Groups`."
msgstr ""
"Log derefter ind med de relevante administratorlegitimationsoplysninger. "
"Klik på :guilabel:`Brugergrupper` i menuen til venstre i Axivox-"
"administrationspanelet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:336
msgid ""
"To add a user group from the :guilabel:`User Groups` page, "
"click :guilabel:`Add a group`."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje en brugergruppe fra siden :guilabel:`Brugergrupper` skal du "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en gruppe`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:338
msgid ""
"Next, name the group, by entering text into the :guilabel:`Name` field. "
"Then, add a member to the group by typing the first few letters of the "
"user's name into the :guilabel:`Members` field. The user populates in a drop-"
"down menu below the field. Then, click on the desired user, and they are "
"added to the user group."
msgstr ""
"Navngiv derefter gruppen ved at indtaste tekst i feltet :guilabel:`Navn`. "
"Tilføj derefter et medlem til gruppen ved at skrive de første par bogstaver "
"i brugerens navn i feltet :guilabel:`Medlemmer`. Brugeren vises i en "
"rullemenu under feltet. Klik derefter på den ønskede bruger, så tilføjes de "
"til brugergruppen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/manage_users.rst:343
msgid "Repeat this process to add more users to the group."
msgstr "Gentag denne proces for at tilføje flere brugere til gruppen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:3
msgid "Voicemails and audio messages"
msgstr "Voicemails og lydbeskeder"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:7
msgid ""
"Managing voicemail is an important part of any business. A company needs to "
"access their messages with ease, and stay on top of any missed calls. "
"Recording audio messages, like thanking a caller for reaching out, or "
"directing them to the right extension, is also a great way to personalize "
"the business interaction, and set the tone with the customer."
msgstr ""
"Håndtering af voicemail er en vigtig del af enhver virksomhed. En virksomhed "
"skal have nem adgang til deres beskeder og holde styr på eventuelle "
"ubesvarede opkald. Optagelse af lydbeskeder, som at takke en opkalder for at "
"række ud eller dirigere dem til den rigtige lokal, er også en god måde at "
"personliggøre forretningsinteraktionen og sætte tonen med kunden."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:12
msgid ""
"This document covers the configuration of both voicemail and audio messages "
"in the Axivox administrative portal."
msgstr ""
"Dette dokument dækker konfiguration af både voicemail og lydbeskeder i "
"Axivox-administrationsportalen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:18
msgid "Set global language"
msgstr "Indstil globalt sprog"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:20
msgid ""
"To start using voicemails and audio messages with Axivox, the global "
"language should be set in the Axivox admin portal settings. To do that, "
"navigate to `manage.axivox.com <axivox_admin_>`_. After logging into the "
"portal, go to :menuselection:`Settings --> Global language (e.g.: voicemail "
"messages,...)`."
msgstr ""
"For at begynde at bruge voicemails og lydbeskeder med Axivox bør det globale "
"sprog indstilles i Axivox-administrationsportalens indstillinger. For at "
"gøre det skal du navigere til `manage.axivox.com <axivox_admin_>`_. Efter "
"login til portalen skal du gå til :menuselection:`Indstillinger --> Globalt "
"sprog (f.eks.: voicemailbeskeder,...)`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:25
msgid ""
"From here, set the language to "
"either: :guilabel:`Francais`, :guilabel:`English`, :guilabel:`Espanol`, "
"or :guilabel:`Deutsch`."
msgstr ""
"Indstil herfra sproget til enten: :guilabel:`Francais`, :guilabel:`English`, "
":guilabel:`Espanol` eller :guilabel:`Deutsch`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:28
msgid ""
"Then, click :guilabel:`Save`, followed by :guilabel:`Apply changes` in the "
"upper-right corner of the :guilabel:`General Settings` page to implement the "
"change into production."
msgstr ""
"Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Gem`, efterfulgt af :guilabel:`Anvend ændringer` "
"i øverste højre hjørne af siden :guilabel:`Generelle indstillinger` for at "
"implementere ændringen i produktion."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:34
msgid "Activate voicemail"
msgstr "Aktiver voicemail"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:36
msgid ""
"In order for a user to utilize voicemail in Axivox, the voicemail feature "
"**must** be turned on in the Axivox administrative portal. To begin using "
"voicemail with a user, navigate to `manage.axivox.com <axivox_admin_>`_. "
"Then, log in with the appropriate administrator credentials."
msgstr ""
"For at en bruger kan benytte voicemail i Axivox, **skal** "
"voicemailfunktionen være slået til i Axivox-administrationsportalen. For at "
"begynde at bruge voicemail med en bruger skal du navigere til "
"`manage.axivox.com <axivox_admin_>`_. Log derefter ind med de relevante "
"administratorlegitimationsoplysninger."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:40
msgid ""
"On the left menu of the Axivox administrative panel, click "
"into :guilabel:`Users`."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Brugere` i menuen til venstre i Axivox-"
"administrationspanelet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:42
msgid ""
"Then, click into the specific user the voicemail should be activated for. "
"Under the section marked, :guilabel:`Voicemail`, open the drop-down menu, "
"and click on :guilabel:`Yes`."
msgstr ""
"Klikněte poté na konkrétního uživatele, pro kterého má být hlasová schránka "
"aktivována. V sekci označené :guilabel:`Voicemail` otevřete rozbalovací "
"nabídku a klikněte na :guilabel:`Yes`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:45
msgid ""
"Lastly, :guilabel:`Save` the change, then click :guilabel:`Apply changes` in "
"the upper-right corner of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Nakonec změnu uložte pomocí :guilabel:`Save` a poté klikněte na "
":guilabel:`Apply changes` v pravém horním rohu obrazovky."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:49
msgid "Voicemail"
msgstr "Hlasová schránka"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:51
msgid ""
"The next step is to set up the individual voicemail boxes on the Axivox "
"administrative portal. To access the portal, visit `manage.axivox.com "
"<axivox_admin_>`_ and log in. Then, navigate to :menuselection:`Voicemails`, "
"located in the menu on the left."
msgstr ""
"Dalším krokem je nastavení jednotlivých hlasových schránek na administračním "
"portálu Axivox. Pro přístup k portálu navštivte `manage.axivox.com "
"<axivox_admin_>`_ a přihlaste se. Poté přejděte na "
":menuselection:`Voicemails`, které najdete v nabídce vlevo."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:55
msgid ""
"If the voicemail option was activated in the user profile, using this "
"process :ref:`voip/axivox/activate_voicemail`, then a voicemail is "
"automatically created on the :guilabel:`Voicemails` page."
msgstr ""
"Pokud byla možnost hlasové schránky aktivována v profilu uživatele pomocí "
"tohoto procesu :ref:`voip/axivox/activate_voicemail`, pak je hlasová "
"schránka automaticky vytvořena na stránce :guilabel:`Voicemails`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:60
msgid ""
"It should be noted that some of the administrative portal language is in "
"French, as Axivox is a Belgian company. The global language is still set to "
"one of the four options as seen here: :ref:`voip/axivox/global_language`."
msgstr ""
"Je třeba poznamenat, že některé části jazyka administračního portálu jsou ve "
"francouzštině, protože Axivox je belgická společnost. Globální jazyk je "
"stále nastaven na jednu ze čtyř možností, jak je vidět zde: :ref:`voip/"
"axivox/global_language`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:65
msgid "Manually create voicemail"
msgstr "Manuální vytvoření hlasové schránky"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:67
msgid ""
"To manually create a new voicemail box, click :guilabel:`Add a voicemail` on "
"the :guilabel:`Voicemails` page. Or, edit an existing voicemail box, by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Edit` to the far-right of an existing voicemail box on "
"the :guilabel:`Voicemails` page."
msgstr ""
"Pro manuální vytvoření nové hlasové schránky klikněte na :guilabel:`Add a "
"voicemail` na stránce :guilabel:`Voicemails`. Nebo upravte existující "
"hlasovou schránku kliknutím na :guilabel:`Edit` zcela vpravo u existující "
"hlasové schránky na stránce :guilabel:`Voicemails`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:72
msgid ""
"Suppose a sales or support team needs a general voicemail box. The voicemail "
"would need to be created manually, and attached to an incoming number."
msgstr ""
"Předpokládejme, že prodejní nebo podpůrný tým potřebuje obecnou hlasovou "
"schránku. Hlasová schránka by musela být vytvořena manuálně a připojena k "
"příchozímu číslu."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:75
msgid ""
"The new, manually-created voicemail box should be attached to an incoming "
"number, so it can receive messages. To do so, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Incoming numbers`, located in the menu on the left. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Edit` to the far-right of the specific number the voicemail "
"should be linked to."
msgstr ""
"Nově manuálně vytvořená hlasová schránka by měla být připojena k příchozímu "
"číslu, aby mohla přijímat zprávy. Pro tento účel přejděte na "
":menuselection:`Incoming numbers`, které najdete v nabídce vlevo. Poté "
"klikněte na :guilabel:`Edit` zcela vpravo u konkrétního čísla, ke kterému má "
"být hlasová schránka připojena."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:80
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Destination type for voice call` field, click the drop-"
"down menu, and select :guilabel:`Voicemail`. Then, open the drop-down menu "
"on the next line labeled, :guilabel:`Voicemail`, and select the manually-"
"created voicemail box."
msgstr ""
"V poli :guilabel:`Destination type for voice call` klikněte na rozbalovací "
"nabídku a vyberte :guilabel:`Voicemail`. Poté otevřete rozbalovací nabídku "
"na dalším řádku označeném :guilabel:`Voicemail` a vyberte manuálně "
"vytvořenou hlasovou schránku."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:85
msgid ""
"If an incoming number is capable of receiving SMS/text messages, an "
"additional field, :guilabel:`Destination email address for Incoming SMS`, is "
"present."
msgstr ""
"Pokud je příchozí číslo schopné přijímat SMS/textové zprávy, je přítomno "
"dodatečné pole :guilabel:`Destination email address for Incoming SMS`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:88
msgid ""
"To determine whether an incoming number is capable of receiving SMS/text "
"messages, click :guilabel:`Incoming numbers` from the menu on the left, then "
"check the :guilabel:`SMS compatible` column for the incoming number."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li zjistit, zda je příchozí číslo schopné přijímat SMS/textové "
"zprávy, klikněte na :guilabel:`Incoming numbers` v nabídce vlevo a "
"zkontrolujte sloupec :guilabel:`SMS compatible` u příchozího čísla."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:92
msgid ""
"Then, if applicable, in the field labeled, :guilabel:`Destination email "
"address for Incoming SMS`, enter an email to which incoming text messages "
"sent to the incoming number can be received. Some incoming numbers (US +1) "
"in Axivox are capable of receiving text messages from individuals and "
"automated numbers."
msgstr ""
"Poté, pokud je to relevantní, do pole označeného :guilabel:`Destination "
"email address for Incoming SMS` zadejte e-mail, na který mohou být přijímány "
"příchozí textové zprávy odeslané na příchozí číslo. Některá příchozí čísla "
"(US +1) v Axivoxu jsou schopná přijímat textové zprávy od jednotlivců a "
"automatizovaných čísel."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:97
msgid ""
"Should this field be left empty, the default destination address is used, "
"instead (as previously set in the beginning of the process for manually "
"creating a voicemail)."
msgstr ""
"Pokud zůstane toto pole prázdné, použije se místo toho výchozí cílová adresa "
"(jak byla nastavena na začátku procesu pro manuální vytvoření hlasové "
"schránky)."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:100
msgid ""
"Once all desired configurations are complete, click :guilabel:`Save`, then "
"click :guilabel:`Apply changes` in the upper-right corner of the screen to "
"implement the change into production."
msgstr ""
"Jakmile jsou dokončeny všechny požadované konfigurace, klikněte na "
":guilabel:`Save`, poté klikněte na :guilabel:`Apply changes` v pravém horním "
"rohu obrazovky, abyste implementovali změnu do produkce."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:104
#: ../../content/applications/productivity/whatsapp.rst:818
msgid "Notifications"
msgstr "Notifikationer"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:106
msgid ""
"Now, whenever a voicemail is received on any of the automatically pre-"
"configured or manually-linked voicemail boxes, an email is sent to the "
"user's email address, as listed in the :guilabel:`Voicemails` page, or in "
"the user's Axivox profile."
msgstr ""
"Nyní, kdykoliv je přijata hlasová zpráva na kteroukoli z automaticky "
"předkonfigurovaných nebo manuálně připojených hlasových schránek, je odeslán "
"e-mail na e-mailovou adresu uživatele, jak je uvedena na stránce "
":guilabel:`Voicemails` nebo v profilu uživatele Axivox."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:110
msgid ""
"This information can be accessed by navigating to :menuselection:`Users` in "
"the left menu, and clicking :guilabel:`Edit` next to the specific user in "
"question."
msgstr ""
"Tyto informace jsou dostupné přechodem na :menuselection:`Users` v levé "
"nabídce a kliknutím na :guilabel:`Edit` vedle konkrétního uživatele."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:116
msgid "Forwarding to voicemail"
msgstr "Přesměrování na hlasovou schránku"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:118
msgid ""
"In Axivox, there are also numerous forwarding settings for a user. To access "
"these forwarding settings, go to `manage.axivox.com <axivox_admin_>`_ and "
"log in."
msgstr ""
"V Axivoxu existuje také řada nastavení přesměrování pro uživatele. Pro "
"přístup k těmto nastavením přesměrování přejděte na `manage.axivox.com "
"<axivox_admin_>`_ a přihlaste se."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:121
msgid ""
"Next, navigate to :menuselection:`Users`, located in the menu on the left."
msgstr ""
"Naviger derefter til :menuselection:`Brugere`, som findes i menuen til "
"venstre."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:123
msgid ""
"From there, click into the specific user the forwarding should be added to. "
"Then, open the :guilabel:`Forwardings` tab."
msgstr ""
"Klik derfra ind på den specifikke bruger, som viderestillingen skal tilføjes "
"til. Åbn derefter fanen :guilabel:`Viderestillinger`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:126
msgid ""
"If the user is busy on another call, or away from the phone, there is an "
"option present in this tab to :guilabel:`Send to voicemail as a last "
"resort`, located in the :guilabel:`Forwarding on no answer` "
"and :guilabel:`Forwarding on busy` fields."
msgstr ""
"Hvis brugeren er optaget af et andet opkald eller væk fra telefonen, er der "
"en mulighed i denne fane for at :guilabel:`Send til voicemail som en sidste "
"udvej`, som findes i felterne :guilabel:`Viderestilling ved intet svar` og "
":guilabel:`Viderestilling ved optaget`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:None
msgid ""
"Send to voicemail as a last resort options highlighted on the Forwardings "
"tab of the user."
msgstr ""
"Send til voicemail som en sidste udvej-muligheder fremhævet på fanen "
"Viderestillinger for brugeren."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:134
msgid ""
"If the :guilabel:`Send to voicemail as a last resort` box is ticked, when "
"the forwarding actions stated in each section are not successful, the caller "
"is routed to the voicemail set on the particular user."
msgstr ""
"Hvis feltet :guilabel:`Send til voicemail som en sidste udvej` er markeret, "
"dirigeres opkalderen til den voicemail, der er indstillet på den pågældende "
"bruger, når viderestillingshandlingerne angivet i hver sektion ikke lykkes."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:139
msgid ""
"For more information on forwarding and transfers, visit :ref:`voip/axivox/"
"forwardings_tab`."
msgstr ""
"For mere information om viderestilling og overførsler, besøg :ref:`voip/"
"axivox/forwardings_tab`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:141
msgid ""
"When all the desired configurations are complete, click :guilabel:`Save`, "
"then click :guilabel:`Apply changes` in the upper-right corner of the screen "
"to implement the change."
msgstr ""
"Når alle ønskede konfigurationer er fuldført, klik på :guilabel:`Gem`, og "
"klik derefter på :guilabel:`Anvend ændringer` i øverste højre hjørne af "
"skærmen for at implementere ændringen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:147
msgid "Audio messages"
msgstr "Talebeskeder"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:149
msgid ""
"It is possible to add audio messages *before* a customer's call is even "
"taken, to inform them about the waiting time for deliveries, the "
"availability of a product, or any other important promotional messages."
msgstr ""
"Det er muligt at tilføje lydbeskeder *før* en kundes opkald overhovedet "
"besvares, for at informere dem om ventetiden for leveringer, "
"tilgængeligheden af et produkt eller andre vigtige salgsfremmende beskeder."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:153
msgid ""
"To record an audio message in Axivox, navigate to `manage.axivox.com "
"<axivox_admin_>`_ and log in."
msgstr ""
"For at optage en lydbesked i Axivox, naviger til `manage.axivox.com "
"<axivox_admin_>`_ og log ind."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:155
msgid ""
"Next, click on :guilabel:`Audio messages` in the menu on the left. From "
"the :guilabel:`Audio messages` page, click :guilabel:`Add a message`."
msgstr ""
"Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Lydbeskeder` i menuen til venstre. Fra siden "
":guilabel:`Lydbeskeder` klik på :guilabel:`Tilføj en besked`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:158
msgid "Type in a :guilabel:`Name`, and click :guilabel:`Save`."
msgstr "Indtast et :guilabel:`Navn`, og klik på :guilabel:`Gem`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:160
msgid ""
"Upon clicking :guilabel:`Save`, the browser redirects back to the "
"main :guilabel:`Audio messages` page, where the newly-created message can be "
"found on the list."
msgstr ""
"Ved klik på :guilabel:`Gem` omdirigerer browseren tilbage til hovedsiden "
":guilabel:`Lydbeskeder`, hvor den nyoprettede besked kan findes på listen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:163
msgid ""
"There are two different ways to make the audio message. The user could "
"either record the message over the phone, or type the message (in text), and "
"select a computer-generated speaker to read the message."
msgstr ""
"Der er to forskellige måder at lave lydbeskeden på. Brugeren kan enten "
"optage beskeden over telefonen eller skrive beskeden (som tekst) og vælge en "
"computergenereret oplæser til at læse beskeden."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:168
msgid "Record audio message"
msgstr "Optag lydbesked"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:170
msgid ""
"To record an audio message over the phone, click the orange button "
"labeled, :guilabel:`Record/Listen`, located to the right of the desired "
"message on the list to record, on the :guilabel:`Audio messages` page."
msgstr ""
"For at optage en lydbesked over telefonen, klik på den orange knap mærket "
":guilabel:`Optag/Lyt`, som er placeret til højre for den ønskede besked på "
"listen på siden :guilabel:`Lydbeskeder`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:174
msgid ""
"When clicked, a :guilabel:`Record / listen to a message` pop-up window "
"appears. From here, the message is then recorded, via one of the extensions "
"that is associated with the user. Under :guilabel:`Extension to use for "
"message management` field, click the drop-down menu, and select the "
"extension where Axivox should call to record the message."
msgstr ""
"Når der klikkes, vises et pop-op-vindue med :guilabel:`Optag / lyt til en "
"besked`. Herfra optages beskeden derefter via en af de linjer, der er "
"knyttet til brugeren. Under feltet :guilabel:`Linje der skal bruges til "
"beskedstyring`, klik på rullemenuen og vælg den linje, hvor Axivox skal "
"ringe for at optage beskeden."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:179
msgid "Then, click :guilabel:`OK` to begin the call."
msgstr "Klik derefter på :guilabel:`OK` for at starte opkaldet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:182
msgid ""
"The user **must** be active in the production database with :abbr:`VoIP "
"(Voice over Internet Protocol)` configured. To configure :abbr:`VoIP (Voice "
"over Internet Protocol)` for a user, see this "
"documentation: :doc:`axivox_config`."
msgstr ""
"Brugeren **skal** være aktiv i produktionsdatabasen med :abbr:`VoIP (Voice "
"over Internet Protocol)` konfigureret. For at konfigurere :abbr:`VoIP (Voice "
"over Internet Protocol)` for en bruger, se denne dokumentation: "
":doc:`axivox_config`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:186
msgid ""
"Upon connecting to the Axivox audio recorder management line, a recorded "
"French-speaking operator provides the following options:"
msgstr ""
"Ved forbindelse til Axivox lydoptager-styringslinje giver en optaget "
"fransktalende operatør følgende muligheder:"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:189
#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:199
msgid "Press `1` to record a message."
msgstr "Tryk på `1` for at optage en besked."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:190
#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:200
msgid "Press `2` to listen to the current message."
msgstr "Tryk `2` for at lytte til den aktuelle besked."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:192
msgid ""
"Press either `1` or `2`, depending on whether or not there is already a "
"message present in the system for this particular audio message that "
"requires a review, before recording a new one."
msgstr ""
"Tryk enten `1` eller `2`, afhængigt af om der allerede findes en besked i "
"systemet for denne specifikke lydbesked, der kræver gennemgang, før en ny "
"optages."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:195
msgid ""
"Record the new audio message after pressing `1`, then press `#` to end the "
"recording."
msgstr ""
"Optag den nye lydbesked efter at have trykket `1`, og tryk derefter `#` for "
"at afslutte optagelsen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:197
msgid ""
"The French-speaking operator returns to the line presenting the first set of "
"questions again:"
msgstr ""
"Den fransktalende operatør vender tilbage til linjen og præsenterer det "
"første sæt spørgsmål igen:"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:202
msgid "Press `#` to end the call."
msgstr "Tryk `#` for at afslutte opkaldet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:205
msgid "Write audio message"
msgstr "Skriv lydbesked"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:207
msgid ""
"To type the message, and select a computerized speaker to say the text, "
"navigate to the :menuselection:`Audio messages` in the menu on the left."
msgstr ""
"For at indtaste beskeden og vælge en computeriseret oplæser til at sige "
"teksten, skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Lydbeskeder` i menuen til "
"venstre."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:210
msgid ""
"From the :guilabel:`Audio messages` page, select the blue button "
"labeled, :guilabel:`Text message`, next to the corresponding audio "
"message :guilabel:`Name` that the message should be attached to."
msgstr ""
"Fra siden :guilabel:`Lydbeskeder` skal du vælge den blå knap mærket "
":guilabel:`Tekstbesked` ved siden af det tilsvarende lydbesked-"
":guilabel:`navn`, som beskeden skal tilknyttes."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:213
msgid "Doing so reveals a :guilabel:`Convert text to message` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Dette viser et pop op-vindue med :guilabel:`Konverter tekst til besked`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:215
msgid ""
"From the :guilabel:`Convert to text message` pop-up window, click the drop-"
"down menu next to the field labeled, :guilabel:`Voice`, and select an option "
"for the :guilabel:`Text` to be read in."
msgstr ""
"Fra pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Konverter til tekstbesked` skal du klikke på "
"rullemenuen ved siden af feltet mærket :guilabel:`Stemme` og vælge en "
"indstilling, som :guilabel:`Teksten` skal læses op med."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:218
msgid ""
"After the :guilabel:`Voice` selection has been made, and the message has "
"been written in the :guilabel:`Text` field, click :guilabel:`Generate` to "
"process the audio file."
msgstr ""
"Efter at :guilabel:`Stemme`-valget er foretaget, og beskeden er skrevet i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Tekst`, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Generer` for at "
"behandle lydfilen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:221
msgid ""
"The text is read in the same language it is written in the :guilabel:`Text` "
"field. Should the language differ in the :guilabel:`Voice` field, then an "
"accent is used by the computerized speaker."
msgstr ""
"Teksten læses op på samme sprog, som den er skrevet i feltet "
":guilabel:`Tekst`. Hvis sproget i feltet :guilabel:`Stemme` er anderledes, "
"bruges en accent af den computeriserede oplæser."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:224
msgid ""
"Finally, when these steps are complete, click :guilabel:`Save` to save the "
"audio message."
msgstr ""
"Når disse trin er fuldført, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme "
"lydbeskeden."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:226
msgid ""
"To implement the changes, click :guilabel:`Apply changes` in the upper-right "
"corner of the screen."
msgstr ""
"For at implementere ændringerne skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Anvend "
"ændringer` i øverste højre hjørne af skærmen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:None
msgid ""
"Convert text to message window with voice, text, generate button and save "
"highlighted."
msgstr ""
"Konverter tekst til besked-vindue med stemme, tekst, generer-knap og gem "
"fremhævet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:233
msgid ""
"To set a greeting or audio message in a dial plan element double-click on "
"the element. This could be a :guilabel:`Play a file` element, or "
"a :guilabel:`Menu` element, in which the caller should encounter an urgent "
"message, or a dial-by-number directory."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille en velkomstbesked eller lydbesked i et opkaldsplandselement "
"skal du dobbeltklikke på elementet. Dette kan være et :guilabel:`Afspil en "
"fil`-element eller et :guilabel:`Menu`-element, hvor den, der ringer, skal "
"møde en hastende besked eller et opkaldskatalog efter nummer."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:237
msgid ""
"For more information on dial plans see this "
"documentation: :doc:`dial_plan_basics` or :doc:`dial_plan_advanced`."
msgstr ""
"For mere information om opkaldsplaner, se denne dokumentation: "
":doc:`dial_plan_basics` eller :doc:`dial_plan_advanced`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:243
msgid "Music on-hold"
msgstr "Ventemusik"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:245
msgid ""
"Axivox has the option to add custom hold music to the call whenever a caller "
"is waiting for their call to be answered. To add hold music to the Axivox "
"administrative portal, navigate to the `manage.axivox.com <axivox_admin_>`_, "
"and log in."
msgstr ""
"Axivox har mulighed for at tilføje tilpasset ventemusik til opkaldet, når en "
"person, der ringer, venter på, at deres opkald bliver besvaret. For at "
"tilføje ventemusik til Axivox-administrationsportalen skal du navigere til "
"`manage.axivox.com <axivox_admin_>`_ og logge ind."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:249
msgid ""
"Then, click on :guilabel:`Music on hold` from the menu on the left, and "
"a :guilabel:`Change the music on hold` pop-up window appears."
msgstr ""
"Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Ventemusik` i menuen til venstre, og et pop op-"
"vindue med :guilabel:`Skift ventemusikken` vises."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:252
msgid ""
"On the :guilabel:`Change the music on hold` pop-up window, click "
"the :guilabel:`Choose File` button to select an MP3 (MPEG Audio Layer 3) or "
"WAV (Waveform Audio File Format ) file to be uploaded."
msgstr ""
"I pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Skift ventemusik` skal du klikke på knappen "
":guilabel:`Vælg fil` for at vælge en MP3 (MPEG Audio Layer 3) eller WAV "
"(Waveform Audio File Format) fil, der skal uploades."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:256
msgid ""
"Only :abbr:`MP3 (MPEG Audio Layer 3)` or :abbr:`WAV (Waveform Audio File "
"Format)` files can be uploaded to the Axivox administrative portal."
msgstr ""
"Kun :abbr:`MP3 (MPEG Audio Layer 3)` eller :abbr:`WAV (Waveform Audio File "
"Format)` filer kan uploades til Axivox administrationsportalen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:259
msgid ""
"Once the file is selected, the :guilabel:`Progression` bar shows an upload "
"status. When this activity completes, the window can be closed, by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Close`."
msgstr ""
"Når filen er valgt, viser :guilabel:`Progression`-bjælken uploadstatus. Når "
"denne aktivitet er fuldført, kan vinduet lukkes ved at klikke på "
":guilabel:`Luk`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/axivox/vm_audio_messages.rst:262
msgid ""
"When the desired changes are complete, click :guilabel:`Apply changes` in "
"the upper-right corner of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Når de ønskede ændringer er fuldført, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Anvend "
"ændringer` i øverste højre hjørne af skærmen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:3
msgid "Devices and integrations"
msgstr "Enheder og integrationer"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:5
msgid ""
":abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` can be used on many different "
"devices, such as a computer, tablet, mobile phone, and many more. This is "
"helpful in that it reduces costs, and employees can work from anywhere in "
"the world, so long as they have a broadband internet connection."
msgstr ""
":abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` kan bruges på mange forskellige "
"enheder, såsom en computer, tablet, mobiltelefon og mange flere. Dette er "
"nyttigt, da det reducerer omkostninger, og medarbejdere kan arbejde fra hvor "
"som helst i verden, så længe de har en bredbånds internetforbindelse."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:9
msgid ""
"Odoo *VoIP* is SIP (Session Initiation Protocol) compatible, which means it "
"can be used with *any* :abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation Protocol)` compatible "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *VoIP* er SIP (Session Initiation Protocol) kompatibel, hvilket "
"betyder, at det kan bruges med *enhver* :abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation "
"Protocol)` kompatibel applikation."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:12
msgid ""
"This document covers the process of setting up Odoo *VoIP* across different "
"devices and integrations."
msgstr ""
"Dette dokument dækker processen med at opsætte Odoo *VoIP* på tværs af "
"forskellige enheder og integrationer."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:15
msgid ""
"Odoo is fully-integrated with all Odoo apps, allowing users to click into "
"any app, and schedule a call as an activity in the chatter."
msgstr ""
"Odoo er fuldt integreret med alle Odoo-apps, hvilket giver brugere mulighed "
"for at klikke ind i en hvilken som helst app og planlægge et opkald som en "
"aktivitet i chatteren."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:19
msgid ""
"For example, in the *CRM* app, a user can click into an opportunity, and "
"click on :guilabel:`Activities` in the chatter."
msgstr ""
"For eksempel i *CRM*-appen kan en bruger klikke ind i en mulighed og klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Aktiviteter` i chatteren."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:22
msgid ""
"Next, they can choose :guilabel:`Call`, and under :guilabel:`Due Date`, they "
"can select a date."
msgstr ""
"Derefter kan de vælge :guilabel:`Opkald`, og under :guilabel:`Forfaldsdato` "
"kan de vælge en dato."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:24
msgid "Once they click :guilabel:`Save`, an activity shows up in the chatter."
msgstr "Når de klikker på :guilabel:`Gem`, vises en aktivitet i chatten."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:26
msgid ""
"Should the :guilabel:`Due Date` be for today's date, the activity shows up "
"in the :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` widget."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :guilabel:`Forfaldsdato` er for dags dato, vises aktiviteten i "
":abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)`-widgetten."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:0
msgid ""
"View of CRM leads and the option to schedule an activity for Odoo Discuss."
msgstr ""
"Visning af CRM-kundeemner og muligheden for at planlægge en aktivitet for "
"Odoo Dialog."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:34
msgid "Odoo VoIP (laptop/desktop computer)"
msgstr "Odoo VoIP (bærbar/stationær computer)"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:36
msgid ""
"The Odoo *VoIP* (Voice over Internet Protocol) module and widget can be used "
"from any browser on a laptop or desktop device. Simply click on "
"the :guilabel:`☎️ (phone)` icon in the upper-right corner, while in the Odoo "
"database, and the widget appears."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *VoIP* (Voice over Internet Protocol) modul og widget kan bruges fra "
"enhver browser på en bærbar eller stationær enhed. Klik blot på "
":guilabel:`☎️ (telefon)`-ikonet i øverste højre hjørne, mens du er i Odoo-"
"databasen, og widgetten vises."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:41
msgid ""
"To see how to use the :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` widget on "
"a desktop/laptop computer, check out this documentation: :doc:`voip_widget`."
msgstr ""
"For at se, hvordan man bruger :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)`-"
"widgetten på en stationær/bærbar computer, se denne dokumentation: "
":doc:`voip_widget`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:45
msgid "Odoo VoIP (tablet/mobile device)"
msgstr "Odoo VoIP (tablet/mobilenhed)"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:47
msgid ""
"The Odoo *VoIP* app can be used on tablets and mobile phones, through the "
"Odoo Android or Apple IOS applications. Additionally, a mobile web browser "
"can be used to access the database."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *VoIP*-appen kan bruges på tablets og mobiltelefoner gennem Odoo "
"Android- eller Apple iOS-applikationerne. Derudover kan en mobil webbrowser "
"bruges til at få adgang til databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:51
msgid ""
"Odoo Android and Apple IOS applications are no longer being maintained by "
"Odoo on the Android and Apple portals. This means Odoo support only handles "
"limited scopes of Odoo Android or Apple IOS support tickets."
msgstr ""
"Odoo Android- og Apple iOS-applikationer vedligeholdes ikke længere af Odoo "
"på Android- og Apple-portalerne. Dette betyder, at Odoo-support kun "
"håndterer begrænsede områder af Odoo Android- eller Apple iOS-"
"supporthenvendelser."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:56
msgid ""
"While outgoing calls can be placed using Odoo on a mobile device, be aware "
"that Odoo is **not** a full :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` "
"application, and does **not** ring on incoming calls. If the user needs to "
"be reachable on a mobile device at all times, an app, like Zoiper, should be "
"used. Apps like that stay connected in the background at all times."
msgstr ""
"Selvom udgående opkald kan foretages ved hjælp af Odoo på en mobil enhed, "
"skal du være opmærksom på, at Odoo **ikke** er en komplet :abbr:`VoIP (Voice "
"over Internet Protocol)`-applikation, og **ikke** ringer ved indgående "
"opkald. Hvis brugeren skal kunne nås på en mobil enhed til enhver tid, bør "
"en app som Zoiper bruges. Sådanne apps forbliver forbundet i baggrunden hele "
"tiden."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:61
msgid "For more information, see this documentation: :ref:`voip/zoiper`."
msgstr "For mere information, se denne dokumentation: :ref:`voip/zoiper`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:63
msgid ""
"While in the mobile application on a mobile device/tablet, access the Odoo "
"*VoIP* widget, by tapping on the :guilabel:`☎️ (phone)` icon in the upper-"
"right corner. The widget appears in the lower-left corner."
msgstr ""
"Mens du er i mobilapplikationen på en mobil enhed/tablet, kan du få adgang "
"til Odoo *VoIP*-widgetten ved at trykke på :guilabel:`☎️ (telefon)`-ikonet i "
"øverste højre hjørne. Widgetten vises i nederste venstre hjørne."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:67
msgid ""
"When first making a call from the tablet using the mobile application, the "
"user is prompted to :guilabel:`Allow` the database to use the microphone. "
"Click :guilabel:`Allow` when prompted to continue with the call using the "
"microphone."
msgstr ""
"Når der første gang foretages et opkald fra tabletten ved hjælp af "
"mobilapplikationen, bliver brugeren bedt om at :guilabel:`Tillad`, at "
"databasen bruger mikrofonen. Klik på :guilabel:`Tillad`, når du bliver bedt "
"om det, for at fortsætte opkaldet ved hjælp af mikrofonen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:71
msgid ""
"This step is **necessary**, whether using the mobile Odoo application or web "
"browser."
msgstr ""
"Dette trin er **nødvendigt**, uanset om du bruger Odoo mobilapplikationen "
"eller webbrowseren."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:None
msgid "Allow the database to access the microphone."
msgstr "Tillad databasen at få adgang til mikrofonen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:77
msgid ""
"Odoo then asks how to make the call. The two options are : :guilabel:`VOIP` "
"or :guilabel:`Phone` (should the tablet be enabled for calling). Click the "
"box next to :guilabel:`Remember ?` should this decision be the default "
"moving forward."
msgstr ""
"Odoo spørger derefter, hvordan opkaldet skal foretages. De to muligheder er: "
":guilabel:`VOIP` eller :guilabel:`Telefon` (hvis tabletten er aktiveret til "
"opkald). Klik på boksen ved siden af :guilabel:`Husk?`, hvis denne "
"beslutning skal være standard fremadrettet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:None
msgid ""
"Window prompt to choose whether to use VOIP or the devices phone to make the "
"call."
msgstr ""
"Vinduesmeddelelse til at vælge, om der skal bruges VOIP eller enhedens "
"telefon til at foretage opkaldet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:85
msgid ""
"Here is the layout of what the Odoo *VoIP* app looks like on a mobile device:"
msgstr "Her er layoutet af, hvordan Odoo *VoIP*-appen ser ud på en mobil enhed:"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:None
msgid "Layout of what the VoIP app looks like on the a mobile device."
msgstr "Layout af, hvordan VoIP-appen ser ud på en mobilenhed."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:94
msgid "Zoiper Lite"
msgstr "Zoiper Lite"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:96
msgid ""
"*Zoiper Lite* is a free :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet "
"Protocol)` :abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation Protocol)` dialer with voice and "
"video."
msgstr ""
"*Zoiper Lite* er en gratis :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` "
":abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation Protocol)`-opkalder med tale og video."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:99
msgid ""
"To start using the *Zoiper* app, download it to the device, via the `Zoiper "
"download page <https://www.zoiper.com/en/voip-softphone/download/current>`_."
msgstr ""
"For at begynde at bruge *Zoiper*-appen skal du downloade den til enheden via "
"`Zoiper-downloadsiden <https://www.zoiper.com/en/voip-softphone/download/"
"current>`_."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:102
msgid ""
"A mobile device is the most common installation, and this document covers "
"how to set up on the *Zoiper* IOS application. Screenshots and steps may "
"differ depending on the set up conditions."
msgstr ""
"En mobil enhed er den mest almindelige installation, og dette dokument "
"dækker, hvordan man opsætter på *Zoiper* IOS-applikationen. Skærmbilleder og "
"trin kan variere afhængigt af opsætningsbetingelserne."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:105
msgid ""
"After installing the *Zoiper* application on the mobile phone, open the "
"application, and tap on :guilabel:`Settings`. Navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Accounts`, and tap on the :guilabel:`+ (plus)` icon to "
"add an account."
msgstr ""
"Efter installation af *Zoiper*-applikationen på mobiltelefonen skal du åbne "
"applikationen og trykke på :guilabel:`Indstillinger`. Naviger til "
":menuselection:`Konti`, og tryk på :guilabel:`+ (plus)`-ikonet for at "
"tilføje en konto."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:109
msgid ""
"If the :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` account is already set "
"up, then click :guilabel:`Yes`. This means an account username and password "
"has already been produced."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)`-kontoen allerede er "
"oprettet, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Ja`. Det betyder, at et "
"kontobrugernavn og adgangskode allerede er oprettet."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:None
msgid "Zoiper account setup, shown in the view from a mobile device."
msgstr "Zoiper kontoopsætning, vist i visningen fra en mobilenhed."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:116
msgid ""
"Next, tap on :guilabel:`Select a provider`. On the screen that populates, "
"tap :guilabel:`Country`, in the upper-right corner, to narrow the providers "
"down to a specific country. Choose the country for the provider that is "
"being configured, then find the :guilabel:`Provider`, and select it."
msgstr ""
"Tryk derefter på :guilabel:`Vælg en udbyder`. På den skærm, der vises, skal "
"du trykke på :guilabel:`Land` i øverste højre hjørne for at indsnævre "
"udbyderne til et bestemt land. Vælg landet for den udbyder, der "
"konfigureres, find derefter :guilabel:`Udbyder`, og vælg den."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:121
msgid ""
"If the provider being configured is *Axivox*, then "
"select :guilabel:`Belgium`. Then, choose :guilabel:`Axivox` as the provider."
msgstr ""
"Hvis den udbyder, der konfigureres, er *Axivox*, skal du vælge "
":guilabel:`Belgien`. Vælg derefter :guilabel:`Axivox` som udbyder."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:None
msgid "Zoiper account setup, choosing the provider."
msgstr "Zoiper kontoopsætning, valg af udbyder."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:128
msgid ""
"Under :abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation Protocol)` options, enter "
"the :guilabel:`Account name`, :guilabel:`Domain`, :guilabel:`Username`, "
"and :guilabel:`Password`. All this information varies, based on the account."
msgstr ""
"Under :abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation Protocol)`-indstillinger skal du "
"indtaste :guilabel:`Kontonavn`, :guilabel:`Domæne`, :guilabel:`Brugernavn` "
"og :guilabel:`Adgangskode`. Alle disse oplysninger varierer afhængigt af "
"kontoen."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:133
msgid ""
"To access this information, via the *Axivox* portal, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Users --> Choose user --> Edit --> SIP Identifiers tab`. "
"The :guilabel:`SIP username`, :guilabel:`Domain`, :guilabel:`SIP password`, "
"and :guilabel:`Address of the proxy server` are all present in this tab."
msgstr ""
"For at få adgang til disse oplysninger via *Axivox*-portalen skal du "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Brugere --> Vælg bruger --> Rediger --> SIP-"
"identifikatorer-fanen`. :guilabel:`SIP-brugernavn`, :guilabel:`Domæne`, "
":guilabel:`SIP-adgangskode` og :guilabel:`Adresse på proxyserveren` er alle "
"til stede i denne fane."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:141
msgid "Zoiper Field"
msgstr "Zoiper-felt"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:142
msgid "Axivox Field"
msgstr "Axivox-felt"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:143
msgid "Account name"
msgstr "Kontonavn"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:144
msgid "*Can be anything*"
msgstr "*Kan være hvad som helst*"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:145
#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:146
msgid "Domain"
msgstr "Domæne"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:147
msgid "Username"
msgstr "Brugernavn"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:148
msgid "SIP username"
msgstr "SIP-brugernavn"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:149
msgid "Password"
msgstr "Adgangskode"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:150
msgid "SIP password"
msgstr "SIP-adgangskode"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:152
msgid ""
"Once this account information is entered, click the "
"green :guilabel:`Register` button at the top of the screen. Once the "
"registration information is checked, *Zoiper* populates a message, "
"stating :guilabel:`Registration Status: OK`."
msgstr ""
"Når disse kontooplysninger er indtastet, klik på den grønne "
":guilabel:`Registrer`-knap øverst på skærmen. Når registreringsoplysningerne "
"er kontrolleret, viser *Zoiper* en meddelelse med teksten "
":guilabel:`Registreringsstatus: OK`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:156
msgid ""
"At this point, *Zoiper* is now set up to make phone calls using "
"the :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` service."
msgstr ""
"På dette tidspunkt er *Zoiper* nu konfigureret til at foretage telefonopkald "
"ved hjælp af :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)`-tjenesten."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:None
msgid "Zoiper account setup, registration successful."
msgstr "Zoiper-kontoopsætning, registrering lykkedes."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:164
msgid "Linphone"
msgstr "Linphone"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:166
msgid ""
"*Linphone* is an open-source :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet "
"Protocol)` :abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation Protocol)` softphone, used for "
"voice, video, messaging (group and individual), as well as conference calls."
msgstr ""
"*Linphone* er en open source :abbr:`VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol)` "
":abbr:`SIP (Session Initiation Protocol)` softphone, der bruges til tale, "
"video, beskeder (gruppe og individuel) samt konferenceopkald."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:170
msgid ""
"To start using the *Linphone* app, download it to the device, via the "
"`Linphone download page <https://new.linphone.org/technical-corner/linphone?"
"qt-technical_corner=2#qt-technical_corner>`_."
msgstr ""
"For at begynde at bruge *Linphone*-appen skal du downloade den til enheden "
"via `Linphone-downloadsiden <https://new.linphone.org/technical-corner/"
"linphone?qt-technical_corner=2#qt-technical_corner>`_."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:173
msgid ""
"A mobile device is the most common installation, and this document covers "
"how to set up the *Linphone* IOS application. Screenshots and steps may "
"differ depending on the circumstances."
msgstr ""
"En mobil enhed er den mest almindelige installation, og dette dokument "
"dækker, hvordan man opsætter *Linphone* IOS-applikationen. Skærmbilleder og "
"trin kan variere afhængigt af omstændighederne."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:176
msgid ""
"To begin configuring *Linphone* for use with a :abbr:`SIP (Session "
"Initiation Protocol)` provider, first open *Linphone*, and an assistant "
"screen appears."
msgstr ""
"For at begynde at konfigurere *Linphone* til brug med en :abbr:`SIP (Session "
"Initiation Protocol)`-udbyder skal du først åbne *Linphone*, hvorefter en "
"assistentskærm vises."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:179
msgid ""
"From this screen, select :guilabel:`Use SIP Account`. Then, on the following "
"screen, enter "
"the :guilabel:`Username`, :guilabel:`Password`, :guilabel:`Domain`, "
"and :guilabel:`Display Name`. Once complete, press :guilabel:`Login`."
msgstr ""
"På denne skærm vælges :guilabel:`Brug SIP-konto`. På den følgende skærm "
"indtastes derefter :guilabel:`Brugernavn`, :guilabel:`Adgangskode`, "
":guilabel:`Domæne` og :guilabel:`Vist navn`. Når det er færdigt, tryk på "
":guilabel:`Login`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:183
msgid ""
"At this point, *Linphone* is ready to start making calls, once there is a "
"green button at the top of the application screen that "
"reads, :guilabel:`Connected`."
msgstr ""
"På dette tidspunkt er *Linphone* klar til at begynde at foretage opkald, når "
"der er en grøn knap øverst på applikationsskærmen, der læser "
":guilabel:`Forbundet`."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:None
msgid "Linphone account setup, registration successful."
msgstr "Linphone-kontoopsætning, registrering lykkedes."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:191
msgid ""
"*Linphone* makes a variety of applications for mobile and desktop devices in "
"operating systems, such as Windows, Linux, Apple, and Android. Because "
"*Linphone* is an open-source project, many new updates are released on a "
"regular basis."
msgstr ""
"*Linphone* laver en række applikationer til mobile og desktop-enheder i "
"operativsystemer såsom Windows, Linux, Apple og Android. Fordi *Linphone* er "
"et open source-projekt, udgives mange nye opdateringer regelmæssigt."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/devices_integrations.rst:195
msgid ""
"See `Linphone's wiki-documentation page <https://wiki.linphone.org/xwiki/"
"wiki/public/view/Linphone/>`_."
msgstr ""
"Se `Linphones wiki-dokumentationsside <https://wiki.linphone.org/xwiki/wiki/"
"public/view/Linphone/>`_."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/onsip.rst:3
msgid "Use VoIP services in Odoo with OnSIP"
msgstr "Brug VoIP-tjenester i Odoo med OnSIP"

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/onsip.rst:6
msgid ""
"OnSIP :abbr:`VoIP (voice over internet protocol)` services are only "
"available in the **United States** (US). OnSIP :abbr:`VoIP (voice over "
"internet protocol)` services are widely available in the lower-48, "
"contiguous United States. In Alaska or Hawaii, charges for service can be "
"higher."
msgstr ""
"OnSIP :abbr:`VoIP (voice over internet protocol)` tjenester er kun "
"tilgængelige i **USA** (US). OnSIP :abbr:`VoIP (voice over internet protocol)"
"` tjenester er bredt tilgængelige i de 48 kontinentale amerikanske stater. I "
"Alaska eller Hawaii kan omkostningerne til tjenesten være højere."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/onsip.rst:10
msgid ""
"Additionally, a :abbr:`US (United States)` billing address, and :abbr:`US "
"(United States)` credit card are required to use the service."
msgstr ""
"Derudover kræves en :abbr:`USA (United States)` faktureringsadresse og et "
":abbr:`USA (United States)` kreditkort for at bruge tjenesten."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/onsip.rst:13
msgid ""
"Before setting up an account with OnSIP, the business will need to make sure "
"the business telephone numbers are portable to OnSIP."
msgstr ""
"Inden der oprettes en konto hos OnSIP, skal virksomheden sikre sig, at "
"virksomhedens telefonnumre kan overføres til OnSIP."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/onsip.rst:16
msgid ""
"OnSIP makes every attempt to work with all telephone service providers. "
"However, certain local or regional guidelines may preclude the company's "
"current provider from releasing the number."
msgstr ""
"OnSIP gør alt for at samarbejde med alle telefonudbydere. Visse lokale eller "
"regionale retningslinjer kan dog forhindre virksomhedens nuværende udbyder i "
"at frigive nummeret."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/onsip.rst:22
msgid ""
"Odoo *VoIP* can be set up to work together with `OnSIP (Odoo Landing Page) "
"<https://info.onsip.com/odoo/>`_. OnSIP is a VoIP provider. An account is "
"needed with OnSIP in order to use this service."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *VoIP* kan konfigureres til at fungere sammen med `OnSIP (Odoo Landing "
"Page) <https://info.onsip.com/odoo/>`_. OnSIP er en VoIP-udbyder. Der er "
"brug for en konto hos OnSIP for at bruge denne tjeneste."

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/voip/onsip.rst:26
msgid ""
"Before setting up an account with OnSIP, make sure the company's home area, "
"and the areas that will be called, are covered by OnSIP services."
msgstr ""
"Inden der oprettes en konto hos OnSIP, skal du sikre dig, at virksomhedens "
